@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Features";
}

<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="text-center mb-5 reveal">
        <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold section-title">All <span class="text-gradient">Features</span></h1>
        <p class="fs-5 mt-3" style="color: var(--gray-500);">Every tool you need to track, reflect, and retain what you learn daily.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 1 -->
    <div class="row align-items-center g-5 mb-5 pb-4">
        <div class="col-lg-6 reveal-left">
            <span class="badge bg-primary bg-opacity-10 text-primary mb-2 rounded-pill px-3 py-2">01 &middot; Core</span>
            <h2 class="fw-bold mb-3 display-6">Activity Tracking</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary fs-5">DayScribe logs the active window title and application name every 2 seconds. It captures browser tabs via a lightweight Chrome extension — no invasive screen recording, just metadata.</p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mt-4">
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Foreground window tracking (2s interval)</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Chrome extension for URL &amp; tab tracking</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Time spent per app, domain, and article</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>SQLite storage — always accessible</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6 text-center reveal-right">
            <div class="feature-mockup p-5 shadow-sm">
                <div class="mockup-dots">
                    <span style="background: #ef4444;"></span>
                    <span style="background: #f59e0b;"></span>
                    <span style="background: #10b981;"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="pt-4">
                    <i class="bi bi-activity display-1 text-primary"></i>
                    <div class="mt-3">
                        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between small text-secondary mb-1">
                            <span>VS Code</span><span>3h 45m</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="progress mb-2" style="height: 8px; background: var(--gray-200);">
                            <div class="progress-bar bg-primary" style="width: 45%; border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between small text-secondary mb-1">
                            <span>Chrome</span><span>2h 10m</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="progress mb-2" style="height: 8px; background: var(--gray-200);">
                            <div class="progress-bar" style="width: 28%; border-radius: 4px; background: var(--accent);"></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between small text-secondary mb-1">
                            <span>Terminal</span><span>1h 05m</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="progress" style="height: 8px; background: var(--gray-200);">
                            <div class="progress-bar bg-success" style="width: 15%; border-radius: 4px;"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 2 -->
    <div class="row align-items-center g-5 mb-5 pb-4 flex-lg-row-reverse">
        <div class="col-lg-6 reveal-right">
            <span class="badge bg-info bg-opacity-10 text-info mb-2 rounded-pill px-3 py-2">02 &middot; Intelligence</span>
            <h2 class="fw-bold mb-3 display-6">AI Daily Digest</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary fs-5">Every evening, DayScribe analyzes your tracked activity and generates a natural-language summary of your day. It identifies top apps, domains, articles read, and key learning topics — all powered by local LLMs via Ollama or optionally OpenAI.</p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mt-4">
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Top apps and time breakdown</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Browsed domains &amp; article titles</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>AI-generated learning highlights</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Choose Ollama (local) or OpenAI</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6 text-center reveal-left">
            <div class="feature-mockup p-5 shadow-sm">
                <div class="mockup-dots">
                    <span style="background: #ef4444;"></span>
                    <span style="background: #f59e0b;"></span>
                    <span style="background: #10b981;"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="pt-4">
                    <i class="bi bi-journal-text display-1 text-info"></i>
                    <div class="mt-3 text-start bg-dark bg-opacity-10 p-3 rounded-3">
                        <p class="small text-secondary mb-1"><strong>DayScribe Digest</strong> &mdash; July 20, 2026</p>
                        <p class="small mb-0">"You spent 4 hours coding, read 3 articles about distributed systems, and explored the new Tailwind CSS v4 docs. Great progress on the microservices project!"</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 3 -->
    <div class="row align-items-center g-5 mb-5 pb-4">
        <div class="col-lg-6 reveal-left">
            <span class="badge bg-success bg-opacity-10 text-success mb-2 rounded-pill px-3 py-2">03 &middot; Privacy</span>
            <h2 class="fw-bold mb-3 display-6">Privacy-First Architecture</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary fs-5">DayScribe is built for privacy from the ground up. All data is stored locally in SQLite. No telemetry, no accounts, no cloud synchronization unless you explicitly configure it. Your data never leaves your machine.</p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mt-4">
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>100% local SQLite storage</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>No accounts or sign-ups required</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Zero telemetry or analytics</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Open source (MIT license)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6 text-center reveal-right">
            <div class="feature-mockup p-5 shadow-sm">
                <div class="mockup-dots">
                    <span style="background: #ef4444;"></span>
                    <span style="background: #f59e0b;"></span>
                    <span style="background: #10b981;"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="pt-4">
                    <i class="bi bi-shield-check display-1 text-success"></i>
                    <div class="mt-3">
                        <div class="d-flex justify-content-center gap-4 flex-wrap">
                            <div class="text-center">
                                <i class="bi bi-laptop fs-2 text-secondary"></i>
                                <p class="small text-secondary mt-1">Your Machine</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="d-flex align-items-center">
                                <i class="bi bi-arrow-right fs-4" style="color: var(--gray-300);"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-center">
                                <i class="bi bi-database fs-2 text-primary"></i>
                                <p class="small text-secondary mt-1">Local SQLite</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="d-flex align-items-center">
                                <i class="bi bi-x-lg fs-4 text-danger"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-center opacity-50">
                                <i class="bi bi-cloud fs-2 text-secondary"></i>
                                <p class="small text-secondary mt-1">Cloud</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 4 -->
    <div class="row align-items-center g-5 mb-5 pb-4 flex-lg-row-reverse">
        <div class="col-lg-6 reveal-right">
            <span class="badge bg-warning bg-opacity-10 text-warning mb-2 rounded-pill px-3 py-2">04 &middot; Reading</span>
            <h2 class="fw-bold mb-3 display-6">Article Summarization</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary fs-5">Read a long article during work? DayScribe's browser extension reports the URL. The built-in article summarizer fetches the content via SmartReader and generates a concise AI summary — so you can revisit key points without re-reading.</p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mt-4">
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>SmartReader content extraction</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>LLM-powered article summaries</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Stored locally for later review</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Works with any paywall-free article</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6 text-center reveal-left">
            <div class="feature-mockup p-5 shadow-sm">
                <div class="mockup-dots">
                    <span style="background: #ef4444;"></span>
                    <span style="background: #f59e0b;"></span>
                    <span style="background: #10b981;"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="pt-4">
                    <i class="bi bi-file-text display-1 text-warning"></i>
                    <div class="mt-3 text-start bg-white bg-opacity-50 p-3 rounded-3">
                        <p class="small fw-bold mb-1">Clean Architecture in .NET</p>
                        <p class="small text-secondary mb-0">"This article explains how to structure .NET applications using Clean Architecture principles with dependency inversion, mediator pattern, and bounded contexts."</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature 5 -->
    <div class="row align-items-center g-5">
        <div class="col-lg-6 reveal-left">
            <span class="badge bg-danger bg-opacity-10 text-danger mb-2 rounded-pill px-3 py-2">05 &middot; Insights</span>
            <h2 class="fw-bold mb-3 display-6">Dashboard &amp; AI Chat</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary fs-5">Visualize your day with charts showing time spent across apps and domains. The AI Chat lets you ask natural-language questions about your data: "What did I work on yesterday afternoon?" or "Summarize the articles I read this week."</p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mt-4">
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Interactive time breakdown charts</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Natural-language AI chat</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Raw activity log viewer</li>
                <li class="mb-3"><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i>Search and filter by date or app</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6 text-center reveal-right">
            <div class="feature-mockup p-5 shadow-sm">
                <div class="mockup-dots">
                    <span style="background: #ef4444;"></span>
                    <span style="background: #f59e0b;"></span>
                    <span style="background: #10b981;"></span>
                </div>
                <div class="pt-4">
                    <i class="bi bi-bar-chart display-1 text-danger"></i>
                    <div class="mt-3 bg-dark bg-opacity-10 rounded-3 p-3">
                        <div class="d-flex align-items-start gap-2">
                            <i class="bi bi-chat-dots text-primary mt-1"></i>
                            <div class="text-start">
                                <p class="small text-secondary mb-1"><strong>You:</strong> What did I learn about Kubernetes?</p>
                                <p class="small mb-0"><strong>DayScribe:</strong> You read 2 articles about Kubernetes — one on pod autoscaling and another on service mesh with Istio.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
